JOHANNESBURG - The African Bank has a new chief executive officer, Basani Maluleke. She was appointed one of African Bank's good bank board of directors in 2015 and became a director last year. READ: Restructured African Bank gets ratings upgrade She has more than a decade of experience in the financial services sector, including a stint at Rand Merchant Bank. Maluleke becomes the first black woman to head up a commercial bank in South Africa. African Bank chairman Louis von Zeuner said Maluleke has been an integral part of executing the bank's turnaround strategy since her appointment as a non-executive in July 2015 and subsequent transition to group executive for operations in July 2017. "We look forward to working with her in her capacity as CEO," he said. Brian Riley retires as CEO. eNCA